    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="687"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 17, 1895</hi>
                        </date>. (Received Jan. 4, 1896.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 728.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose for your information
                    the translation of the only note from the Sublime Porte ever written in response
                    to my repeated demands for the protection of Americans.</p>
                <p>Telegraphic orders were usually directed in my presence, after the verbal demand
                    with which my notes were accompanied.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 728.—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <persName type="from">Tevfik Pasha</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to"
                                >Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Sublime Porte</hi>
                            </placeName>,<lb/>
                            <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-02">
                                <hi rend="italic">December 2, 1895</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Envoy</hi>: In reply to the note your excellency
                        has kindly addressed to me on the 18th ultimo, No. 99, I hasten to inform
                        you that the Sublime Porte, which had already invited the provincial
                        authorities to use the greatest vigilance for the protection of all the
                        foreign subjects in the Empire, has just renewed to the said authorities, in
                        the most earnest manner, its instructions in the same sense.</p>
                    <p>Please accept, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tevfik.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
